vitessio/vitess#18591.body:
### Overview of the Issue

Occasionally, calling `show vitess_shards;` will return an immediate error. Looking at the code, this is on purpose - it expects to cache errors, and if there is a lastErr within the cache interval, we will return it instead of going back to the source and trying to find the answer:

```go
// If it is not time to check again, then return either the cached
// value or the cached error but don't ask topo again.
// Here we have to be careful with the part where we haven't gotten even the first result.
// In that case, a refresh is already in progress, but the cache is empty! So, we can't use the cache.
// We have to wait for the query's results.
// We know the query has run at least once if the insertionTime is non-zero, or if we have an error.
queryRanAtLeastOnce := !entry.insertionTime.IsZero() || entry.lastError != nil
if !shouldRefresh && queryRanAtLeastOnce {
	if cacheValid {
		return entry.value, nil
	}
	return nil, entry.lastError
}
```

I don't think this is right, we have this effectively singleflighted already - all of this is locked, and we collapse requests down into one goroutine's worth of refreshing, so (I think) it should be harmless to fall back and refresh when we have an error instead of returning a cached one. 

### Reproduction Steps

This is an intermittent issue that we have not been able to produce fully in the lab, but reading the code shows how it is possible. 

### Binary Version

```sh
This has been experienced on various builds of Vitess 21/22.
```

